snippet.textDisplay:
I think mouthguards are good, but only protect against bacterial infection or, in connection with influenza and corona, against the secondary bacterial infections that are the main cause of death from viral infections.
So mouthguard is still very important in the coronavirus pandemic.
Effective protection against virus infections such as Influenza or corona virus infections would only be vaccination.
However, new, previously unknown virus pathogens are always lacking the vaccine.
Countries such as China, the USA, Germany and France are therefore working intensively on the development of vaccines.
Since the production, especially in Germany, can and will always take months and even longer than a year due to bureaucratic approval procedures, my suggestion would be:
In Germany, you should form a team of experts (virologists, pharmacologists, laboratory technicians, etc.) and fly with the Air Force's jumbo jet, which has been converted into a flying laboratory, near the pandemic centers in China (Wuhan region).
On site, the German team of experts can help Chinese doctors and researchers with vaccine development and production. This could greatly accelerate vaccine development and production and save many lives.
This is in the interest of all countries around the world, which should support this project as much as possible (financially, materially, personally).
The pandemic is a global threat and must therefore be combated with united global forces.

Robert Koch also went to Egypt with French doctors and helped fight cholera there.

Vaccine must be developed as soon as possible.
The stupid sayings of 'We can do it' or 'The danger is low for Germany' should be stopped.
Calming doesn't help.
Action must now be taken.
